								<h2>
										<img src="http://www.higheredexperts.com/work/img/icon-fulltime.png" alt="full time" />
					 Web Engineer (LAMP/Drupal) 
				</h2>
				<p>
					<span class="fading">at</span>
										<a href="http://www.stevens.edu/">Stevens Institute of Technology</a>
															<span class="fading">in</span> <strong>New York</strong>
									</p>
				<div id="job-description">
				Job Description<br /><br />The Web Engineer/Developer is responsible for developing and supporting a network of websites and web-enabled applications in both Drupal and in the LAMP stack. The successful candidate will provide expertise in the design, development, testing and support of various web applications and systems, and will serve as a key administrator of our enterprise Drupal content management system. The Web Engineer/Developer will work collaboratively and in a team-oriented environment with various constituencies throughout the University including other web/application developers, however they must be able to work in a self-initiated manner when necessary as well in accomplishing their work.<br /> <br />Essential responsibilities:<br />Implement and maintain content management systems including the installation, configuration, troubleshooting, adaptation and modification of Drupal 7.x<br />Design, implement and deploy web based applications and websites from initial design and architecture through development, test and deployment<br />Administer Drupal Core 7.x and Modules<br />Manage migrations of websites and applications from development to production<br />Provide basic systems administration of the LAMP-stack web servers<br />Architect and/or Develop various solutions for stakeholder needs, following policies and standards for system development, as well as project management methodology.<br /> <br />Desired Skills & Experience<br /><br />Required Qualifications:<br />At least a Bachelors Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Information Systems or similar field directly relevant to the responsibilities of the position<br />At least 4-5 years of professional web development experience<br />Fluency in HTML, CSS and JavaScript<br />Advanced to expert level knowledge of PHP and MySQL<br />Advanced knowledge of Drupal 7.x administration and development<br />Candidates who are active contributors within the Drupal community will be favorably considered<br />Basic Linux/Unix systems administration experience<br />Knowledge of LDAP and Shibboleth authentication is a plus<br />Excellent communication skills, both written and oral<br />Teamwork, collaboration, and a strong service ethic are essential<br />Strong desire to work in a fast-paced, collaborative and challenging environment.<br /> <br />About Us<br /><br />Founded in 1870, Stevens Institute of Technology, The Innovation University®, lives at the intersection of industry, academics and research. The University's students, faculty and partners leverage their collective real-world experience and culture of innovation, research and entrepreneurship to confront global challenges in engineering, science, systems and technology management.<br /><br />• Stevens is ranked in the top 3% of Universities for net student ROI (Return on Investment) Bloomberg Businessweek<br />• Stevens' WebCampus online learning unit has been ranked #2 in the nation by US News & World Report's 2010 survey.<br />• Stevens has been ranked by Forbes.com at #3 among US research universities for the high percentage of return on its research investment. <br />• Stevens’ Howe School ranked in national Top 10 for research excellence in Management of Technology by the Journal of Product Innovation Management.<br />• Hoboken was named among the 20 Best College Towns in the US by The Princeton Review.<br />• Stevens has been designated as the first DoD-funded University Affiliated Research Center (UARC) focused on Systems Engineering Research.<br />• Stevens has been named 2008 Jostens Institution of the Year by the Eastern College Athletic Conference.<br />• Stevens' Office of Career Development has been ranked in the Top 20 nationally by The Princeton Review.<br /><br />To Apply: https://www2.apply2jobs.com/Stevens/ProfExt/index.cfm?fuseaction=mExternal.showJob&RID=8193&CurrentPage=1, or use contact below.
				</div><br />
